{
  "text": "ERIC-PCR technique gave 4 different genetic profiles for mycobacteria (Figure 1 ). It should be emphasized that three of these genetic profiles are consistent with those reported in molecular epidemiology studies by amplifying sequences ERIC [CITATION_1] . From 34 isolates clustered in the complex of M. tuberculosis, seven of these 4 make up the genetic profiles obtained by ERIC-PCR. Then they expect the rest of the isolates (27 isolates) that make up this complex terms grouped in the 4 genetic profiles (A, B, C and D) obtained by ERIC-PCR.",
